In 1967 he moved on as a record producer, artist manager (1968), record label owner : Rockburgh Records (1977) and producer manager : Worlds End Management Company (1980) witch moved to Los Angeles in 1985. name: Josef Pasternack
comments: Conductor and composer, born in Poland When he became 10 years old he entered the Warsaw Conservatory of Music, where he studied piano and composition. While he was there he was also studying a different instrument each month, by the time he left the conservatory he could play every instrument in the orchestra except the harp. At age 15 he came to the United States with his two brothers and father. Initially he worked in a hotel restaurant as a busboy and not much later as violonist in the hotel band. In 1902, he was hired as violinist with the Metropolitan Opera Orchestra in New York and then became first viola player, continuing until 1909. Starting in 1916 he was musical director of the Victor Talking Machine Company (later RCA Victor) with Rosario Bourdon, where he worked with Enrico Caruso and Marian Anderson.
